         <abstract>
            <p>Let A(2r + 1, n) denote the n Ã— n band matrix, of bandwidth 2r + 1, with the binomial coefficients in the expansion of (x - 1)&lt;sup&gt;2r&lt;/sup&gt; as the elements in each row and column. Using the fact that the rows of A(2r + 1, n) provide the coefficients for the 2rth central difference, a number of properties of A(2r + 1, n) are obtained for all positive integers r and n. These include obtaining explicit formulas for &lt;tex-math&gt;$\det A(2r + 1, n), A^{-1}(2r + 1, n),||A^{-1}(2r + 1, n)||_\infty$&lt;/tex-math&gt; and an upper triangular matrix U such that A(2r + 1, n)U is lower triangular.</p>
          </abstract>
